A valid for-loop statement in Actian 4GL has the following syntax:
```
for (variable_name = start_value; variable_name <= end_value; variable_name += increment) {
    [statementlist]
}
```
Where `variable_name` represents any valid variable name in Actian 4GL, `start_value` is a number or string that the variable is set to on its first iteration, `end_value` is a number or string that the variable is set to when the loop stops iterating, and `increment` is the change made to the variable after each iteration. Here are some examples of valid expressions:
```
for (i=1; i<=10; i+=1) {
    print "Hello!";
}
for (str = "abc"; str <= "xyz"; str += 1) {
